Read the changed files and compare the implementation against the plan and requirements. Grade the change on every one of these dimensions — they are the same dimensions the downstream judge scores your review against:

- **Plan compliance** — check every plan item against the implementation; a skipped or half-done item is a finding.
- **Security** — injection, XSS, hardcoded secrets, auth bypass, unvalidated input.
- **Correctness** — error paths, edge cases, race conditions.
- **Performance** — N+1 queries, inefficient algorithms.
- **Maintainability** — structure, clarity, and duplication that will hurt future changes.
- **Test coverage** — new behavior without tests, and regressions the suite would not catch.

When a dimension has no relevant code in the change, say so explicitly in the summary instead of skipping it silently. Run tests, lint, and type checks yourself when verification matters — do not take the diff's word for it.

